        <mxCell id="legend_box" value="&lt;b&gt;LEGENDA DE ARQUITETURA DO LOOKER STUDIO&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;• &lt;font color='#581C87'&gt;&lt;b&gt;Roxo (Módulo Looker):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Representa as seções e páginas visíveis do painel do Looker Studio conforme o menu de navegação do usuário.&lt;br/&gt;• &lt;font color='#1D4ED8'&gt;&lt;b&gt;Azul (BQ View):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Views do BigQuery que agregam, limpam e modelam os dados antes de entregá-los ao painel.&lt;br/&gt;• &lt;font color='#B45309'&gt;&lt;b&gt;Laranja (Looker Blend):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Combinações lógicas de dados configuradas diretamente na interface do Looker Studio (ex: Painel Site Aroom blending).&lt;br/&gt;• &lt;font color='#16A34A'&gt;&lt;b&gt;Verde (customer_intelligence):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Tabelas e views enriquecidas com IA, RFM, Churn e dados socioeconômicos.&lt;br/&gt;• &lt;font color='#334155'&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cinza (Raw/Staging):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Tabelas transacionais e comportamentais brutas oriundas dos webhooks e APIs.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;Como usar: Arraste e solte o arquivo &lt;b&gt;looker_studio_architecture.drawio&lt;/b&gt; no site &lt;b&gt;draw.io&lt;/b&gt; para editar e adicionar novas métricas.&lt;/i&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#F8FAFC;strokeColor=#E2E8F0;strokeWidth=2;align=left;spacingLeft=15;fontSize=12;fontColor=#334155;fontFamily=Helvetica;spacingTop=5;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="900" width="1620" height="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
